I"}<p>Like the <a href="http://www.leancrew.com/all-this/2013/12/tweaking-bigfoot-footnotes/">good doctor</a>, I knew as soon as I saw <a href="http://www.bigfootjs.com">Bigfoot</a> that I would be adding it to this site. <sup id="fnref:1"><a href="#fn:1" class="footnote">1</a></sup> I’ve avoided footnotes up till now because the HTML formatting for them seemed far too <em>fiddley</em>, and the Jekyll Markdown processor I was using did not support them.</p>

